---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import siteCopy from '../../data/siteCopy.json';
import MasterLocationMap from '../../components/maps/MasterLocationMap.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Location — Mavrikiano & Vrouchas, Elounda | Elounda Traditional Homes"
  description={siteCopy.metaDescriptionLocation}
  canonicalUrl="https://traditional-homes.gr/en/location/"
>

  <div class="site-max site-pad py-12 md:py-16">

    <nav class="text-xs text-muted mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center gap-1.5" role="list">
        <li><a href="/en/" class="hover:text-body-text transition-colors duration-150">Home</a></li>
        <li aria-hidden="true">›</li>
        <li class="text-body-text font-medium" aria-current="page">Location</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-body-text mb-4">Location</h1>
      <p class="section-sub mb-10">
        Two villages on the hillside above Elounda, northeast Crete.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-10 mb-14">
      <div class="lg:col-span-3 space-y-8">

        <section aria-labelledby="mavrikiano-heading">
          <h2 id="mavrikiano-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl text-body-text mb-3">Mavrikiano</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            A small traditional village perched on the hillside above Elounda town. The ten stone houses are located here, spread along the village lanes. The village is quiet, with no tourist infrastructure of its own — restaurants, shops, and beaches are a short drive down to Elounda.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Most of the houses have open views toward Elounda Bay and the island of Spinalonga, with the Mirabello Gulf beyond.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            To discover the best local beaches, historical sites, and a recommended day-trip itinerary, read our comprehensive <a href="/en/guide/mavrikiano/" class="underline hover:text-amber-800 transition-colors font-medium">Mavrikiano Area Guide &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="vrouchas-heading">
          <h2 id="vrouchas-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl text-body-text mb-3">Vrouchas</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Located above Spinalonga, Vrouchas is a peaceful hillside village offering elevated, uninterrupted views across the Aegean Sea, the magnificent Cretan mountains, and sweeping olive groves. <a href="/en/houses/almond-tree-villa/" class="underline hover:text-amber-800 transition-colors font-medium">Almond Tree Villa</a> sits within this quiet terrain, commanding a vantage point that requires a car for access. A five-minute drive (4.2 km) descends to the shoreline of Plaka, a coastal settlement of pristine pebble beaches and traditional waterfront tavernas where boats depart for the island fortress.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            For recommended day-trip itineraries, detailed boat schedules, and navigating the local terrain, explore our <a href="/en/guide/vrouchas/" class="underline hover:text-amber-800 transition-colors font-medium">Vrouchas & Plaka Area Guide &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="distances-heading">
          <h2 id="distances-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl text-body-text mb-3">Distances</h2>
          
          <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-3">From Mavrikiano Houses</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm mb-8">
            {[
              { label: 'Center of Elounda (Schisma)', value: '3 min drive / 10 min walk' },
              { label: 'Plaka village & Spinalonga boats', value: '7 min drive (4.1 km)' },
              { label: 'Sunken City of Olous', value: '5 min drive (1.8 km)' },
              { label: 'Agios Nikolaos town', value: '19 min drive (11.8 km)' },
              { label: 'Heraklion Airport (HER)', value: '1 hr 2 min drive (67.9 km)' },
            ].map(({ label, value }) => (
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between py-2.5 border-b border-stone-200 gap-4">
                <span class="text-stone-700">{label}</span>
                <span class="text-muted text-right flex-shrink-0">{value}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-800 mb-3">From Vrouchas Villa</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            {[
              { label: 'Plaka village & Spinalonga boats', value: '5 min drive (4.2 km)' },
              { label: 'Center of Elounda (Schisma)', value: '12 min drive (9 km)' },
              { label: 'Sunken City of Olous', value: '15 min drive (10.5 km)' },
              { label: 'Agios Nikolaos town', value: '25 min drive (20.1 km)' },
              { label: 'Heraklion Airport (HER)', value: '1 hr 15 min drive (63.2 km)' },
            ].map(({ label, value }) => (
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between py-2.5 border-b border-stone-200 gap-4">
                <span class="text-stone-700">{label}</span>
                <span class="text-muted text-right flex-shrink-0">{value}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-5">Times are approximate road distances. We do not guarantee specific journey times.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">For detailed walking and driving times to local restaurants, beaches, and landmarks, please refer to our <a href="/en/guide/mavrikiano/" class="underline hover:text-amber-800 transition-colors">Area Guides</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="getting-here-heading">
          <h2 id="getting-here-heading" class="font-serif text-2xl text-body-text mb-3">Getting here</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-body-text mb-1">By car (recommended)</p>
              <p>A rental car is the most practical option. The E75 and regional roads connect Heraklion and Sitia airports to the Elounda area. Detailed directions and GPS coordinates are sent with your booking confirmation.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-body-text mb-1">By bus</p>
              <p>KTEL buses run between Heraklion and Agios Nikolaos; local buses connect Agios Nikolaos and Elounda. The Elounda bus stop is at the bottom of the hill — a taxi or walk uphill is needed from there.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-body-text mb-1">Taxis</p>
              <p>Taxis are available from both airports and from Agios Nikolaos. We can provide local taxi contact information on request.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>

    <section id="map-section" aria-labelledby="interactive-map-heading" class="mt-8 border-t border-stone-200 pt-12">
      <h2 id="interactive-map-heading" class="font-serif text-3xl text-body-text mb-6">Interactive Map</h2>
      <MasterLocationMap />
    </section>

  </div>

</Base>
